        "management": "Supportive care: salt and fluid restriction. Diuretics for edema/hypertension (furosemide). Antihypertensives (CCB or beta-blocker). Penicillin to eradicate any residual infection (no effect on GN). Monitor creatinine, BP, urine output. Spontaneous recovery in >95% children. Adults may have incomplete recovery."
